    {
      "sort": 300000,
      "name": "SHIFT key (both)",
      "type": "text",
      "_id": "8JRDCc5CePLRMFxN",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>By default when clicking a Check Roll (skill, trait etc) a dialogue box opens asking for things like modifiers. Pressing SHIFT and clicking stops this box from appearing and uses no modifiers (unless set by something else in the game).</p><p>Toggling this option on changes this behaviour so that the default is that no box appears, and using SHIFT + click causes the box to appear.</p><p>This is set separately by the person playing the game and can be different for each player.</p><p></p><p>This <strong>does not</strong> apply to Horse damage where the SHIFT key is used to apply charging damage.</p>"
      },
      "video": {
        "controls": true,
        "volume": 0.5
      },
      "src": null,
