    {
      "sort": 400000,
      "name": "Critical Bonus Adjustment (GM only)",
      "type": "text",
      "_id": "xvSMxXzJeG1DEqE2",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>When an opposed or combat roll is made and all parties have a critical bonus due to scores of 20+ then all parties bonuses are reduced by the lowest bonus.<br /></p><p>For example, two knights with Sword Skills of 20 (+3) and 20 (+5) would see their Skills reduced to 20 and 20 (+2), respectively.  This rule has the effect of putting equally-proficient characters on a more even footing with fewer critical successes overall.</p>"
      },
